{"title_page": "Kjerstin Boge Sol\u00e5s", "text_new": "{{short description|Norwegian handball player}}\n{{Infobox handball biography\n| name                = Kjerstin Boge Sol\u00e5s\n| image               = 2016 Women's Junior World Handball Championship - Group A - HUN vs NOR - (046).jpg\n| nationality         = Norwegian\n| birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|1997|12|31|df=y}}\n| birth_place         = [[Dale, Sogn og Fjordane|Dale]], [[Norway]]\n| height              = {{height|m=1.82|precision=0}}\n| position            = Left back\n| currentclub         = [[Si\u00f3fok KC]]\n| clubnumber          = \n| years1              = 2013\u20132015\n| clubs1              = Dale IL\n| years2              = 2015\u20132019\n| clubs2              = [[Tertnes HE]]\n| years3              = 2019\u20132020\n| clubs3              = [[Si\u00f3fok KC]]\n| years4              = 2020\u2013\n| clubs4              = [[By\u00e5sen HE]]\n| nationalyears1      = 2016\u2013\n| nationalteam1       = [[Norway women's national handball team|Norway]]\n| nationalcaps1       = 14\n| nationalgoals1      = 4\n| medaltemplates      = \n{{MedalCompetition|[[European Women's Handball Championship|European Championship]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2016 European Women's Handball Championship|2016 Sweden]]|}}\n}}\n\n'''Kjerstin Boge Sol\u00e5s''' (born 31 December 1997) is a Norwegian [[handball]] player for [[Si\u00f3fok KC]] and the [[Norway women's national handball team]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.handball.no/regioner/nhf-sentralt/kampaktivitet/landslag/handballjentene/til-golden-league/ |title=Til Golden League |publisher=[[Norwegian Handball Federation]] |accessdate=30 September 2016 |language=Norwegian}}</ref>\n\nShe also represented Norway in the [[2016 Women's Junior World Handball Championship]], placing 5th<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ihf.info/files/CompetitionData/9cb0d63b-e3a5-48b7-85d3-aec6c4270280/pdf/NOR.pdf|title=Team Roaster Norway|publisher=[[International Handball Federation|IHF]]|accessdate=21 February 2017|language=English}}</ref>, at the [[2015 Women's Under-19 European Handball Championship]], placing 6th<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eurohandball.com/ech/19/women/2015/match/1/054|title=2015 Women's European Championship 19 Match Details|publisher=[[European Handball Federation|EHF]]|accessdate=31 July 2019|language=English}}</ref> and at the [[2014 Women's Youth World Handball Championship]], placing 13th.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ihf.info/files/CompetitionData/3e98f057-97e0-496f-89c6-5468479cb541/pdf/NOR.pdf/|title=Team Roaster Norway|publisher=[[International Handball Federation|IHF]]|accessdate=21 February 2017|language=English}}</ref>\n\n==Achievements==\n*'''[[European Women's Handball Championship|European Championship]]'''\n**''Winner'': 2016\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Si\u00f3fok KC squad}}\n{{Norway squad 2016 European Women's Handball Championship}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Solas, Kjerstin Boge}}\n[[Category:1997 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Fjaler]]\n[[Category:Norwegian female handball players]]\n\n{{Norway-handball-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Norwegian handball player}}\n{{Infobox handball biography\n| name                = Kjerstin Boge Sol\u00e5s\n| image               = 2016 Women's Junior World Handball Championship - Group A - HUN vs NOR - (046).jpg\n| nationality         = Norwegian\n| birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|1997|12|31|df=y}}\n| birth_place         = [[Dale, Sogn og Fjordane|Dale]], [[Norway]]\n| height              = {{height|m=1.82|precision=0}}\n| position            = Left back\n| currentclub         = [[Si\u00f3fok KC]]\n| clubnumber          = \n| years1              = 2013\u20132015\n| clubs1              = Dale IL\n| years2              = 2015\u20132019\n| clubs2              = [[Tertnes HE]]\n| years3              = 2019\u2013\n| clubs3              = [[Si\u00f3fok KC]]\n| nationalyears1      = 2016\u2013\n| nationalteam1       = [[Norway women's national handball team|Norway]]\n| nationalcaps1       = 14\n| nationalgoals1      = 4\n| medaltemplates      = \n{{MedalCompetition|[[European Women's Handball Championship|European Championship]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2016 European Women's Handball Championship|2016 Sweden]]|}}\n}}\n\n'''Kjerstin Boge Sol\u00e5s''' (born 31 December 1997) is a Norwegian [[handball]] player for [[Si\u00f3fok KC]] and the [[Norway women's national handball team]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.handball.no/regioner/nhf-sentralt/kampaktivitet/landslag/handballjentene/til-golden-league/ |title=Til Golden League |publisher=[[Norwegian Handball Federation]] |accessdate=30 September 2016 |language=Norwegian}}</ref>\n\nShe also represented Norway in the [[2016 Women's Junior World Handball Championship]], placing 5th<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ihf.info/files/CompetitionData/9cb0d63b-e3a5-48b7-85d3-aec6c4270280/pdf/NOR.pdf|title=Team Roaster Norway|publisher=[[International Handball Federation|IHF]]|accessdate=21 February 2017|language=English}}</ref>, at the [[2015 Women's Under-19 European Handball Championship]], placing 6th<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eurohandball.com/ech/19/women/2015/match/1/054|title=2015 Women's European Championship 19 Match Details|publisher=[[European Handball Federation|EHF]]|accessdate=31 July 2019|language=English}}</ref> and at the [[2014 Women's Youth World Handball Championship]], placing 13th.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ihf.info/files/CompetitionData/3e98f057-97e0-496f-89c6-5468479cb541/pdf/NOR.pdf/|title=Team Roaster Norway|publisher=[[International Handball Federation|IHF]]|accessdate=21 February 2017|language=English}}</ref>\n\n==Achievements==\n*'''[[European Women's Handball Championship|European Championship]]'''\n**''Winner'': 2016\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Si\u00f3fok KC squad}}\n{{Norway squad 2016 European Women's Handball Championship}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Solas, Kjerstin Boge}}\n[[Category:1997 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]