{"title_page": "Marshall Broadcasting Group", "text_new": "{{Infobox company\n| name = Marshall Broadcasting Group, Inc.\n| type = [[Privately held company|Private]]\n| industry = [[Terrestrial television|Broadcast Television]]<br>[[Production company|Television Production]]\n| founded = {{Start date and age|2014|12|1}}\n| hq_location_city = [[Houston]], [[Texas]]\n| hq_location_country = [[United States]]\n| area_served = [[Iowa]], [[Illinois]], [[Louisiana]] and Texas\n| key_people = Pluria Marshall, Jr.<br>(President/[[Chief Executive Officer|CEO]])\n| products = [[Broadcast television]]\n| owner = Pluria Marshall, Jr.\n| website = {{Official website|https://mbgroup.tv/}}\n}}\n'''Marshall Broadcasting Group, Inc.''' is an [[United States|American]] television broadcasting company that owns three full power television stations in [[Iowa]], [[Louisiana]] and [[Texas]]. The company was founded on December 1, 2014 by Pluria Marshall, Jr. All three of its television stations are affiliated with [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] and are operated through [[local marketing agreement|shared services agreements]] by [[Nexstar Media Group]].\n\n==History==\nThe company is owned by Pluria Marshall, Jr., who also owns Wave Community Newspapers, a group of African-American community newspapers in the Los Angeles region. Marshall had attempted to acquire stations in the 1990's and 2000's, but faced difficulties securing financing.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nIn 2014, Nexstar Broadcasting Group acquired the stock of television operators [[Grant Broadcasting]], [[Communications Corporation of America]], and [[White Knight Broadcasting]]. Due to FCC ownership limits, Nexstar sold former Grant station [[KLJB]] in [[Davenport, Iowa]], and former ComCorp stations [[KPEJ-TV]] in [[Odessa, Texas]] and [[KMSS-TV]] in [[Shreveport, Louisiana]], all three of which are Fox affiliates, to Marshall Broadcasting Group. Nexstar operates all three of the television stations through a [[local marketing agreement|shared services agreement]], providing non-programming resources to the stations such as [[master control]], advertising sales and engineering support.<ref name=\"tvncmarshall\">{{cite web|url=http://www.tvnewscheck.com/article/76865/nexstar-selling-3-fox-affils-for-585-million|title=Nexstar Selling 3 Fox Affils For $58.5 Million|date=2014-06-06|website=TVNewsCheck|accessdate=2015-04-22}}</ref><ref name=\"b&c-marshall\">{{cite web|url=http://www.broadcastingcable.com/news/local-tv/nexstar-plans-sale-three-fox-affiliates-585-million/131616|title=Nexstar Plans Sale of Three Fox Affiliates For $58.5 Million|last=Malone|first=Michael|date=2014-06-06|website=[[Broadcasting & Cable]]|accessdate=2016-07-02}}</ref>\n\nOn April 3, 2019, the company filed a lawsuit against Nexstar Media Group for breach of contract, alleging that the company used the sale of these stations to minority owners as a ploy to gain favor with the FCC for the associated transactions, but had been engaging in conduct (including withholding [[retransmission consent]] fees) intended to \"undermine\" the company, so that its stations could be repurchased by Nexstar for a lower cost \"[with] significantly less regulatory push-back\" under the current political climate.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bizjournals.com/dallas/news/2019/04/03/marshall-broadcasting-group-claims-in-lawsuit-that.html|title=Marshall Broadcasting Group claims Nexstar 'undermined' prospects in new suit|last=Butler|first=Anna|date=2019-04-03|website=Dallas Business Journal|access-date=2019-04-04}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/biz/news/nexstar-sued-black-owned-tv-company-1203179793/|title=Nexstar Accused of Sabotaging Black-Owned TV Station Group|last=Maddaus|first=Gene|date=2019-04-03|website=Variety|language=en|access-date=2019-04-04}}</ref>\n\nOn December 3, 2019, Marshall Broadcasting Group filed for [[Chapter 11]] bankruptcy protection.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bizjournals.com/houston/news/2019/12/26/the-week-in-bankruptcies-7-companies-file-for.html|title=The week in bankruptcies: 7 companies file for bankruptcy protection in Houston|date=2019-12-26|website=Houston Business Journal|access-date=2019-12-29}}</ref>\n\n==Stations==\nCurrent Marshall Broadcasting Group properties include:\n\n{| class=\"toccolours\" border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse\"\n|- style=\"vertical-align: top; text-align: center;\"\n!style=\"background: #e3e3e3;\"| [[City of License]] / [[Media market|Market]]\n!style=\"background: #e3e3e3;\"| Station\n!style=\"background: #e3e3e3;\"| Channel<br>[[Virtual channel|TV]] ([[Digital terrestrial television|RF]])\n!style=\"background: #e3e3e3;\"| Owned Since\n!style=\"background: #e3e3e3;\"| Current Affiliation\n!style=\"background: #e3e3e3;\"| [[Nexstar Media Group|Nexstar]] Station(s)<br>(Network Affiliation)\n|- style=\"vertical-align: top; text-align: left;\"\n| [[Davenport, Iowa]] / [[Quad Cities]]\n| '''[[KLJB]]'''\n| 18 (49)\n| December 1, 2014<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://licensing.fcc.gov/cgi-bin/ws.exe/prod/cdbs/forms/prod/cdbsmenu.hts?context=25&appn=101663777&formid=905&fac_num=54011|title=Consummation Notice for KLJB|website=CDBS Public Access|publisher=[[Federal Communications Commission]]|access-date=2015-04-22}}</ref>\n| [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]]\n| '''[[WHBF-TV]]''' ([[CBS]])<br>'''[[KGCW]]''' ([[The CW]])\n|- style=\"vertical-align: top; text-align: left;\"\n| [[Shreveport, Louisiana]]\n| '''[[KMSS-TV]]'''\n| 33 (34)\n| January 1, 2015<ref name=\"kmss_kpej_sold\">{{Cite web|url=https://licensing.fcc.gov/cgi-bin/ws.exe/prod/cdbs/forms/prod/cdbsmenu.hts?context=25&appn=101667018&formid=905&fac_num=12524|title=Consummation Notice for KMSS-TV/KPEJ-TV|website=CDBS Public Access|publisher=[[Federal Communications Commission]]|access-date=2015-04-22}}</ref>\n| Fox\n| '''[[KTAL-TV]]''' ([[NBC]])<br>'''[[KSHV-TV]]''' ([[MyNetworkTV]])<sup>1</sup>\n|-style=\"vertical-align: top; text-align: left;\"\n| [[Odessa, Texas|Odessa]] / [[Midland, Texas]]\n| '''[[KPEJ-TV]]'''\n| 24 (23)\n| January 1, 2015<ref name=\"kmss_kpej_sold\" />\n| Fox\n| '''[[KMID (TV)|KMID]]''' ([[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]])\n|}\n\n*<sup>1</sup> KSHV-TV is owned by [[White Knight Broadcasting]] but operated by Nexstar under a separate [[local marketing agreement|SSA]] from KMSS-TV.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|https://mbgroup.tv/}}\n\n[[Category:2014 establishments in Texas]]\n[[Category:American companies established in 2014]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Houston]]\n[[Category:Media companies established in 2014]]\n[[Category:Nexstar Media Group]]\n[[Category:Television broadcasting companies of the United States]]\n[[Category:Companies that filed for Chapter 11 bankruptcy in 2019]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox company\n| name = Marshall Broadcasting Group, Inc.\n| type = [[Privately held company|Private]]\n| industry = [[Terrestrial television|Broadcast Television]]<br>[[Production company|Television Production]]\n| founded = {{Start date and age|2014|12|1}}\n| hq_location_city = [[Houston]], [[Texas]]\n| hq_location_country = [[United States]]\n| area_served = [[Iowa]], [[Illinois]], [[Louisiana]] and Texas\n| key_people = Pluria Marshall, Jr.<br>(President/[[Chief Executive Officer|CEO]])\n| products = [[Broadcast television]]\n| owner = Pluria Marshall, Jr.\n| website = {{Official website|https://mbgroup.tv/}}\n}}\n'''Marshall Broadcasting Group, Inc.''' is an [[United States|American]] television broadcasting company that owns three full power television stations in [[Iowa]], [[Louisiana]] and [[Texas]]. The company was founded on December 1, 2014 by Pluria Marshall, Jr. All three of its television stations are affiliated with [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] and are operated through [[local marketing agreement|shared services agreeme